{"title":"2025 Bespoked UK: Sentient Workshop Project Arion Apocalypse Cargo Bike – john watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/sentient-workshop-apocalypse-cargo-bike/","date":1746086409000,"content":"<p><em>In our Reportage yesterday, we showcased the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-apocalypse-build-off/\" target=\"_blank\">2025 Bespoked UK Apocalypse Build-Off</a>, and today, we’re showcasing the winning bike by Sentient Workshop. There was so much thoughtfulness poured into this design that we had to give it its own <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/beautiful-bicycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Beautiful Bicycles</a> gallery. Let’s get to it!</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.tailfin.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Tailfin</a> for supporting our 2025 Bespoked UK coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Tullen and James run <a href=\"https://sentient.works/\" target=\"_blank\">Sentient Workshop</a>, the UK distributor for <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/omnium/\" target=\"_blank\">Omnium Cargo Bikes</a> located in the South of Wales. Within their workshop, they manufacture everything from frame bags to cargo straps, but their entry into the Apocalypse Build-Off ushers in a new wave of production for the two: their first bike.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-38.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-38.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-38.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-38.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>I asked if anyone had ridden in the cargo bucket yet, and their friend Abi offered to hop in for a photo…</em></p>\n<p>Sentient followed the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-apocalypse-build-off/#:~:text=for%20Bespoked%20exhibitors.-,The%20bike%20must%20have%3A,-Wheels\" target=\"_blank\">Bespoked Apocalypse Build-Off guidelines</a>, following all of the protocols laid out by Konstantin from Drust, who is also part of the Bespoked team, down to the booklet, which is uploaded in the gallery above. Apocalypses can come in various forms, and every civilization has recorded its version of the end of days throughout written history.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-01-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-01-3k.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-01-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-01-3k.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-27-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-27-3k.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-27-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-27-3k.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-02-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-02-3k.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-02-3k.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bespoked25-BestApocalypse-Sentient-02-3k.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>Bespoked UK award studio photos by the ever-talented <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/adamgassonphoto/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Adam Gasson</a></em></p>\n<p>Not only did Sentient create an excellent entry to the contest, but they also imagined a whole narrative that leads to the demise of mankind. In this imaginary world, scientists breed a hybrid species of wax worm and slug that were designed to break down carbon fiber waste. The world had filled with this material that is difficult to recycle. It seems slugs already consume “C” words like cabbages, cucumbers, and so why not carbon?</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-26.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-26.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The mutant slugs have developed a taste for lithium batteries and begin eating people’s AirPods while still inside their ears. Cybertrucks are trashed (yay), and all cell phones are destroyed. It’s now the Dark Ages in London. Meanwhile, Tullen and James read the r/publicfreakout thread on Reddit. They’re safe for now. Not wasting time, the two get to work on designing a bike for the apocalypse.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-5.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-5.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>They begin sketching out the bike in 3D, rendering the elevations, and cobbling together an old Bicycle Academy jig to house this lengthy beast. As the slugs head from London, the two feel a new sense of urgency, so they dive head-first into selecting the tubes. The primary tubing is all Reynolds 525, including a 1 mm-thick Reynolds 525 boom tube and remnants from older bikes they’ve cut up in the workshop.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-15.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-15.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-17.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-17.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-16.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-16.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>After mitering and minimal prep-work, the tubing went into the modified Bicycle Academy jig, and they started welding the front section of the frame. Bear in mind, the two had never built a bike before. But the 1 mm thick tube allowed for a solid proving platform with minimal heat distortion. There were some globby welds filling in gaps, but honestly, I didn’t notice it until they pointed it out. I was too distracted by the steering linkages!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-21.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-21.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-26.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-26.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, the 3D CAD model provided an accurate design for creating 2D drawings of fittings to attach the cargo box to the downtube, as well as the rear rack supports. The dropouts and burly, overbuilt chainstay yoke were crucial solutions as well. Being resourceful with what they had in the shop, they used scrap Omnium CXC forks to complete the bike’s structure.</p>\n<p>It was actually all going to work.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-35.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-35.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-35.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-35.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-36.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-36.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Sourcing rims and hubs – including a generator hub – the wheels were built from spare spokes, as their spoke cutter was broken. Wanting to integrate the generator lamp into the boom tube, they had some 4×4-inspired lighting covers 3D printed and wired up some LED lights. Not wanting to attract the mutant slugs with a lithium battery to power the saw, the two rigged up a bottle dynamo to power a work light for their pedal-powered kindling saw, which is attached to an ammo box and bolted to the rear rack.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-22.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-22.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>When the bike is in a kickstand, you can pedal it to power the saw, the bottle dynamo gets positioned onto the tire, and the saw’s light turns on. It’s genius. The sliding dropouts provide chain tension for the 5-speed Sturmey Archer hub, and the additional cog on the axle drives the saw. (The chain was removed for the Apocalypse competition.)</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-40.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-40.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-40.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-40.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Once the bike was completed, Sentient gave it a Cerakote finish, in-house. They built it up using used parts and explained that once they return back to their workshop, they’ll put a less shitty suspension fork on it and better parts overall. The bike is very nimble and just plows up and over curbs with ease. Is this a masterpiece? Yes, I’d say so…</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Bespoked-UK-Sentient-Apocalypse-Cargo-Bike-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This is by far the most ambitious undertaking and remains one of my fondest moments in documenting framebuilder showcases of all time.</p>\n<p>Tullen and James are legends, and I’m grateful to have their work of art featured here. Well done, lads.</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://sentient.works/\" target=\"_blank\">Sentient Workshop</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/sentient.works/\" target=\"_blank\">@SentientWorks.</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>As a thank you to the builders for their time and energy, I’ve uploaded all of these images to <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/frdx3u2u8awirb5lm3k5u/AP4r3iLUHtJzDySWFi7yLvc?rlkey=oqnccin9ogkdrzhvykma5rnko&amp;st=z92n8d8d&amp;dl=0\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist’s Dropbox</a> for your use! Thanks again, James and Tullen!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Tailfin_logo_2025_Bespoked_UK_size.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.tailfin.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Tailfin</a> for supporting our 2025 Bespoked UK coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/sentient-workshop-apocalypse-cargo-bike/\">2025 Bespoked UK: Sentient Workshop Project Arion Apocalypse Cargo Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3786071cc5a495d5132572f234644110b89dafbe28986151019eec82366fede3","category":"Cycling"}